          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>Even more evidence has come to light that suggests the next Nintendo Direct event could take place very soon. Reliable leaker NateTheHate2 has backed up the <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/nintendo-direct-coming-this-september-report/1100-6534229/" data-ref-id="1100-6534229">initial reports</a> of the next Nintendo Direct coming in September, <a href="https://x.com/natethehate2/status/1962214416339833244?s=46" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">saying</a>, "Yes, there is a Nintendo Direct in September."</p><p>But when? The leaker said fans can expect it during the second week of September. He said it's likely to happen on September 11 or 12. That matches up with a previous report that the event could happen on September 12, which is one day before the 40th anniversary of the release of 1985's original Super Mario Bros.</p>



    
